    {
      "id": 17,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "ISCM View - InfoSec Continuous Monitoring",
      "gridPos": {"x": 0, "y": 24, "w": 24, "h": 6},
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## ISCM: InfoSec Continuous Monitoring View\n\n**Definition**: ISCM provides real-time, automated monitoring of security controls and compliance posture through continuous data collection, analysis, and alerting.\n\n### Continuously Monitored Metrics\n\n| Metric | Panel ID | Monitoring Purpose |\n|--------|----------|-----|\n| Request Volume | Panel 1, 16 | Baseline traffic monitoring |\n| Security Actions | Panels 2, 3 | DLP blocking/redacting activity |\n| HIPAA Events | Panels 5, 9 | PHI detection and protection |\n| FERPA Events | Panels 6, 10 | Educational record protection |\n| High Severity | Panels 4, 11 | Incident detection |\n| Alerts | Panel 15 | Trigger count from security events |\n| Event Timeline | Panel 8 | Temporal security analysis |\n| Log Volume | Panel 14 | System activity overview |\n| Endpoint Analysis | Panel 12 | Attack surface visibility |\n| Incident Details | Panel 13 | Forensic investigation support |\n\n### ISCM Principles Demonstrated\n\n1. **Continuous**: 30-second refresh interval ensures real-time visibility\n2. **Automated**: PostgreSQL queries run automatically via Grafana provisioning\n3. **Integrated**: Single dashboard combining compliance + security monitoring\n4. **Actionable**: Alert counts and high-severity event tables enable response\n5. **Auditable**: All queries source from persistent logs table with timestamps\n\n### NIST SP 800-137 Compliance\n\n| ISCM Requirement | Dashboard Evidence |\n|----------------|-------------------|\n| Continuous security monitoring | All panels show real-time metrics |\n| Security control assessment | Policy decisions, HIPAA/FERPA panels |\n| Security impact analysis | High severity events over time |\n| System state monitoring | Log volume, endpoint activity |\n\n**Data Source**: PostgreSQL `logs` table\n**Refresh Rate**: 30 seconds\n**Time Range**: Adjustable (1h, 6h, 12h, 24h, 7d, 30d)\n\n*This ISCM dashboard demonstrates continuous monitoring capabilities for senior design evaluation.*"
      }
    }
